nts1.d: Founders of Lagos’ new-age underground festival, FREEWATER, join NTS for a 6-show residency, diving deep into the next wave of Nigerian music. Each hour-long show explores our favorite jams from the city’s bubbling alternative scene, covering alt-afro, indie, electronic, and trap sounds shaping the future of Lagos’ underground.

Coined by DRB LasGidi in 2014, alté fuses afrobeats, pop, rap, R&B, soul and dancehall into a DIY, genre‑bending sound from Lagos’ creative fringes. The term - slang for “alternative” - celebrates freedom of expression, emerging as a youth‑led reaction to conservative Naija culture. Catch our guide featuring trailblazers Cruel Santino, Odunsi (The Engine), Amaarae, Tems, and more.
Pattern Sounds co-founder Selassie TBC delivers an hour of straight jams every month.

Charisse C takes us on a monthly journey through an electronic soundscape birthed by the melting pot which raised her, anchored by South African giants Amapiano & Gqom, featuring soulful, bass-heavy & playful selections.

nts1.n: RUF DUG - live from The Dub Techno Chess Club
nts1.d:
Ruf Dug brings the leftfield: old video game soundtracks, dusty analogue dreamers and poolside Balearic sounds. No nonsense from the original tropical cyberpunk.
From the host: "Recorded live at The Dub Techno Chess Club - a regular night at Rainy Heart in Manchester."

nts1.n: KUTMAH PRESENTS: The Last Sketchbook w/ ALIA
nts1.d: Sketchbook was the LA beat night started by Kutmah back in 2004 and was the breeding ground for artists like Daedelus, Ras G, Dibiase, Georgia Anne Muldrow, Teebs and Flying Lotus. Now it's radio reincarnation is on this side of the Atlantic. Lock in.
A monthly sonic journey from Lukid a.k.a Luke Blair. Expect a slow-burning, cinematic hour of hip-hop, epic psych, dub and synth soundscapes.
Ziggy Devriendt is the DJ behind Nosedrip. Tune in once a month for an expert selection of any or all of the following: new age, new wave, French psych, minimal synth, post-punk and a whole lot else…

nts1.n: OKONKOLE Y TROMPA W/ PAM & MÉLANIE MATRANGA (R)
nts1.d:
My Favorite Things Will Never Rot. The first hour of this program loosely reflects on W.G. Sebald's 1995 novel 'The Rings of Saturn', as well as the hit tune from the Sound Of Music, 'My Favorite Things'. It is followed by a guest mix by French artist Mélanie Matranga.
It features extracts from Grant Gee's 2012 film 'Patience (After Sebald)'

nts1.n: NTS Guide to: Hydeout Productions and Friends (R)
nts1.d: Laid back hip hop instrumentals from Hydeout Productions, the label and compilation series celebrating the work of Nujabes and similar artists.

DJ: “… I don’t know, I didn’t… I didn’t think I’d be the one holding the air, I never spoke live before the event consumed the many. I’ve no news for the desperate survivors and… and I can’t… well, I can hope that this next song might help us survive a little longer…"

Youarelistening.to mixes ambient music with police scanner radio, air-traffic control, numbers stations, spoken word & a bunch of other random things. Found footage, musique concrete, and the perfect ambience.
From the host: "Moving up the coast to Vancouver, BC. Listening in on the harbor marine radio, as a winter storm approaches."

nts1.n: THE ONE GLOVE BREAKFAST SHOW W/ MACCA
nts1.d: Stay left and take a trip with Macca's Saturday breakfast show on NTS. Weekend musings and eclectic cuts from all over the place, it's a low-key affair and you're all invited. ONE GLOVE!!!

Ross Allen knows music. Mainly new but plenty of old. The broadest range of music that moves dance floors from across the era’s and across the planet. On his regular Foundation Music Specials he invites guests to share their histories and seminal tracks…
Manchester's Tarzsa brings good vibes Soul, RnB & Jazz to the NTS airwaves once a month.

nts1.d: Long time record collector and purveyor of fine musical flavours Mr. Pedro cooks up a banquet of aural delights every other week: afrobeat to disco and more, time to liven up.

nts2.d: Carolina Soul is a record seller based in Durham, NC, USA. They specialize in rare and classic soul, boogie, gospel and modern obscure tracks from the Carolinas and beyond, mixed with all-time bangers and ballads.

nts2.n: Scenic Route w/ Theo & Mark William Lewis
nts2.d: Special guest shows from around the world.
The South London postpunk crew take control sharing an hour of selections every month.

Olivia O. — musician, multidisciplinary artist, performing under Lowertown, Olivia O., and child star — delivers a set blending cult discoveries, current obsessions, and deep cuts from her collaborators and the NYC underground.
From the host: "An eclectic mix of Holiday Cheer, Screamo,  Folk , Jazz & other good tracks guest starring Avsha (Olivia's best friend and fellow bandmate of Lowertown)"

Lesser heard sounds with a focus on femmes in punk from artist and musician Sara A.
From the host: "This month's show focuses on all-girl garage groups with some femme-fronted sunshine pop and psych mixed in there. Tune in for an hour of moody and melodramatic songs

nts2.n: NTS Guide to: World Music Library (R)
nts2.d: Highlights from Japanese label King Records' subsidiary World Music Library series. Released on CD through the 1990s, World Music Library is an almost peerless collection of professionally recorded, CD-quality performances of world traditional musics. The series predominantly features music from Asia, and notably boasts a rich offering of Javan and Balinese gamelan recordings.

nts2.n: MACHINES OF LOVING GRACE W/ MIDWIFE
nts2.d:
Midwife’s multi-instrumentalist and recording engineer Madeline Johnston presents “Machines of Loving Grace,” a monthly transmission featuring her new finds and old favorites with a focus on the golden age of DIY community, cosmic sentimentalism, world music, and experimental pop. “Machines of Loving Grace” is a gateway into Johnston’s process and personal soundtrack.
Inspired by the Richard Brautigan poem, Midwife’s curated playlists explore the idea of “a cybernetic ecology;” acoustic and electronic sources reflect on our humanity as well as our animalistic nature in the context of a digital landscape.

nts2.n: CRY LATER W/ TROPIC OF CANCER
nts2.d:
Camella Lobo, aka Tropic of Cancer, takes to the air once a month for Cry Later. Tune in for a dedication hour of songs selected by listeners in honor of their lovers and loved ones. Send a personal message and song selection to cryinglater@gmail.com
From the host: _"It's Christmas on Cry Later - a place where joy is found in tinsel-tinged melancholy and memories of better times remind us of what we might find again someday." _

During 'Wave Form', Aurélien Arbet and Pierre Rousseau explore an interpolation of various recordings, often at the margins of traditional formats and conventional styles of music. During an hour, a long oscillation is formed out of a selection of interviews, spoken word, poetry, music for dance or art, marginal pop attempts and various field recordings.
Aurélien Arbet is an art director, co-founder of the clothing brand and publishing house Études. Pierre Rousseau is a composer, producer and sound designer, crafting sounds for records, films, and art projects.

subtle.d: Get ready to embark on a captivating sonic journey of underground music with Charlie Kelly. Including new and timeless sounds from the depths of rap, drill, grime, and experimental genres from the vibrant streets of the UK and beyond. Charlie unearths the very best in music that pushes boundaries. Off the mic, Charlie is a Radio Producer and Social Media Executive with an eclectic music taste spanning across many different cultures, decades, and styles. Hailing from North London with a love for audio and pop culture, you can expect to hear tune after tune when you’re locked into Charlie Kelly on Subtle.
BirdE brings an hour of the freshest Drum and Bass covering everything from liquid to techy steppers - the deeper the better.

Originally from Cambridge, Counter Culture's selection deftly navigates across a myriad of influences and exclusives from himself & friends.
Expect some of the freshest rolling soul straight to your headspace.

subtle.n: Strictly Business Show w/ Qua Rush & Flipz MC
5 Decades of Dub w/ Joe Vincent

subtle.d: casual_observer is a DJ and producer originally hailing from Amsterdam, where he co-organises the "moving closer" event series with friend and collaborator Bcl-2. He currently resides in Berlin. Starting his musical journey as a drummer, his music retains a heavy focus on groove, rhythm and experimentation.  Sets played by casual_observer are diverse and surprising, moving effortlessly between jungle, breaks, bass, footwork, and more. No matter the genre, his selection is sure to keep you on your toes!

In:flux Audio are a record label based in Leeds, UK founded by production duo Tik&Borrow. Since the label's inception in October 2013, they have dabbled in multiple dance music styles with the emphasis always being on the tracks being unique, and packed full of bass. Today the primary output for the label is from their Dubstep roster and this is focus of their show on Subtle - giving the artists and remixers chance to showcase their sounds with an hour guest mix, all hosted by label bossman Tik.

I’m a 19 year old DJ and producer from Newcastle upon Tyne, mainly playing and producing music around the 140bpm mark. I started out playing old 2-step and jungle records, before moving my focus to mainly dubstep and grime. Along with my friends Pirata and White Label, I run Newcastle’s only current 140 night, Well Irie.

subtle.n: THE CULTURE HEAD w. SAINT VOX

subtle.d: DIGDIS presents a selection of tracks that captures the vibrant and ever-evolving edges of dance music. Each show features a wide range of music that can be enjoyed both on the dancefloor and in more intimate listening spaces.

My show focuses on percussive, club sounds, taking inspiration from the edges of drill, funky and bass music. In both my mixes and productions, I like to keep the energy high and a little whimsical. Expect some moments of ambient and R&B too, just so we can all catch our breath.
With a monthly show on Subtle, Niceup is a London based DJ with a unique style. Pushing UKG, Breakbeat, Bass, Electro and 140. Weaving through genres showcasing new releases and older cuts.

Jedah started DJ'ing at the tender age of 18 years of age specialising in UK Garage/Grime. 

Jedah is currently the DJ for Grime Original Hollowman Jendor of the former Grime Collective Essentials/ OG's.

Responsible for “that massive grime tune with the Psycho strings”, UK producers/DJs Trends & Boylan are well versed in what the scene has to offer. They use this platform to showcase music from across the 140 spectrum from Grime to Dubstep. Anything goes!!

XOSÉ is a DJ and aspiring producer mixing and making mostly UK Garage, Grime and UK Funky. FORWARD PRESSURE largely focuses on the aforementioned UK born genres, though you can expect a variety of UK influenced sounds.

Sempra is a producer & DJ based in London, specialising in the fusion of UK Garage, Jungle and Breakbeat with dreamy vocal melodies and the beautiful instrumentation found in Soul and contemporary RnB. Sempra’s consistent output has been released by labels such as Future Classic and Headroom, gaining industry support from the likes of Nia Archives, Sherelle, Yung Singh and Dr Dubplate.

Cicely is a northern raised London based music photographer and DJ. From learning to mix during lockdown, she has since played at clubs across the country in venues such as Fabric, Corsica and Fold.

Cicely runs a collective and events night under the name NRG CRU which focus heavily on the high energy rave sound. She is highly influenced by the northern sound she grew up with, and you can hear this within her sets. Expect heavy blends of techno and hardcore while she shines the light on her favourite northern artists.

Live & Direct is the show that promises to make you dance and make you laugh, with your fave tunes that make you go 'Rahhh ain't hear this in time' and all the cheesy jokes from me, Hannah :) Lock in for the sickest guests and the most relatable stories about daily slips and hilarious situations I find myself in.

Bristol-born and London-based, Not Bad For A Girl resident DaiSu has been involved in the music scene since 2018 and has featured on stations such as Radio 1 Dance, BBC 6 Music and Melodic Distraction, as well as playing on line ups for Keep Hush, Skiddle and Red Bull. Her penchant for bass, breaks and 2-step has landed her gigs supporting acts such as Interplanetary Criminal, Main Phase, Craigie Knowes and Big Ang. In September 2022, her debut EP ‘Lightwork’ was released with Gather Records and was featured in DJ Mag's staff picks that same month.

Sometimes it gets dark, sometimes I try to mix techno awkwardly, sometimes i get nostalgic… I like stuff that’s dreamy, ghostly, pretty and sad. I’ll try out new productions of my own, as well. I’m keeping it pretty open and we’ll see how it evolves.” – Jimmy
